{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Some moral philosophers, political scientists and weapons specialists believe armed, unmanned aircraft offer marked moral advantages over almost any other tool of warfare.", "abstract": "News analysis; some moral philosophers, political scientists and weapon specialists believe armed, unmanned aircraft offer marked moral advantages over almost any other tool of warfare, which may be surprising to those who criticize the use of drones; drones may actually reduce the number of civilian casualties, and the intensified scrutiny of their use in targeted killings may reflect a growing intolerance to the routine slaughter of previous wars.", "section_name": "Sunday Review", "print_page": "4", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Scott", "role": "reported", "lastname": "SHANE", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By SCOTT SHANE", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/15/sunday-review/the-moral-case-for-drones.html", "lead_paragraph": "Some moral philosophers, political scientists and weapons specialists believe armed, unmanned aircraft offer marked moral advantages over almost any other tool of warfare.", "headline": {"seo": "The Moral Case for Drones", "main": "The Moral Case for Drones", "print_headline": "The Moral Case For Drones", "content_kicker": "News Analysis", "kicker": "News Analysis"}, "_id": "53f8cbde38f0d84410bca76d", "word_count": "1026", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2012/07/15/sunday-review/15DRONES/15DRONES-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2012/07/15/sunday-review/15DRONES/15DRONES-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 330, "url": "images/2012/07/15/sunday-review/15DRONES/15DRONES-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2012/07/15/sunday-review/15DRONES/15DRONES-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "330"}, "subtype": "xla